Key Match Events: Tunisia earned a 1-0 victory over Malawi through a late penalty kick by Youssef Msakni
Post-Match Reflections: Tunisia coach Jalal Qaderi praised his team's tactical prowess and concentration
Malawi coach Patrick Mabedi was satisfied with his team's performance and emphasized the importance of grooming replacements for the future
Miscellaneous Highlights: The referee awarded Tunisia the penalty kick after Malawi defender Lawrence Chaziya received a yellow card for fouling an attacker in the box
Others: Tunisia leads the qualifying group with 6 points while Malawi sits third with 3 after four matches
Malawi's next match is against Sao Tome and Principe on June 3, 2024
